 {"id":"beads_rust-1hof","title":"Version command enhancement: br version --check with build info","description":"# Version Management and Display

## Scope
Enhance `br version` command with rich build info and update checking.

## Deliverables
- `br version` - Show version, git commit, build date, features
- `br version --check` - Check if update available (exit 0=up-to-date, 1=update available)
- `br version --json` - Output version info as JSON
- `br version --short` - Output only version number (for scripts)
- Build info embedded at compile time via build.rs
- Feature flags displayed (e.g., +rustls, +mimalloc)

## Version Output Format
```
br 1.0.0 (abc1234 2026-01-20)
Features: +rustls +mimalloc
Rust: 1.75.0, Target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- `br version` shows commit hash and build date
- `br version --check` correctly detects when update available
- `br version --json` outputs valid JSON with all fields
- Build info embedded without network calls at runtime
- Exit codes are script-friendly (0=success, 1=update-available)

## Unit Tests (src/cli/commands/version.rs)
- test_version_format: verify output format
- test_version_json_schema: verify JSON output schema
- test_version_short: verify --short outputs only version
- test_build_info_present: verify git commit and date present
- test_feature_flags: verify features displayed correctly

## E2E Tests (tests/e2e_version.rs)
- e2e_version_output: run br version, verify format
- e2e_version_json: run br version --json, parse JSON
- e2e_version_short: run br version --short, verify single line
- e2e_version_check_uptodate: verify exit 0 when up-to-date
- e2e_version_check_outdated: mock older version, verify exit 1
- e2e_version_no_network: verify basic version works offline

## Build System Requirements
- build.rs to embed git commit hash
- build.rs to embed build timestamp
- build.rs to detect feature flags

