 {"id":"beads_rust-1k9","title":"Performance Benchmarks","description":"## Overview
Implement performance benchmarks using criterion to ensure br meets performance targets and to track performance across releases.

## Technical Requirements

### Benchmark Setup
```rust
// benches/storage_perf.rs
use criterion::{black_box, criterion_group, criterion_main, Criterion, BenchmarkId};

fn benchmark_create(c: &mut Criterion) {
    let mut group = c.benchmark_group("create");

    for size in [10, 100, 1000, 10000].iter() {
        group.bench_with_input(
            BenchmarkId::from_parameter(size),
            size,
            |b, &size| {
                b.iter_batched(
                    || setup_db(),
                    |mut storage| {
                        for i in 0..size {
                            let title = format!("Issue {}", i);
                            storage.create_issue(&title, IssueType::Task, 2).unwrap();
                        }
                    },
                    BatchSize::SmallInput,
                );
            },
        );
    }

    group.finish();
}

fn benchmark_list(c: &mut Criterion) {
    let mut group = c.benchmark_group("list");

    // Pre-populate databases of different sizes
    for size in [100, 1000, 10000].iter() {
        let storage = setup_db_with_issues(*size);

        group.bench_with_input(
            BenchmarkId::from_parameter(size),
            &storage,
            |b, storage| {
                b.iter(|| {
                    black_box(storage.list_issues(ListQuery::default()).unwrap())
                });
            },
        );
    }

    group.finish();
}

fn benchmark_ready_query(c: &mut Criterion) {
    let mut group = c.benchmark_group("ready");

    // Complex dependency graph
    for (issues, deps) in [(100, 200), (1000, 2000), (10000, 20000)].iter() {
        let storage = setup_db_with_deps(*issues, *deps);

        group.bench_with_input(
            BenchmarkId::new("issues_deps", format!("{}_{}", issues, deps)),
            &storage,
            |b, storage| {
                b.iter(|| {
                    black_box(storage.get_ready_issues(ReadyFilters::default()).unwrap())
                });
            },
        );
    }

    group.finish();
}

criterion_group!(
    benches,
    benchmark_create,
    benchmark_list,
    benchmark_ready_query,
);
criterion_main!(benches);
```

### Performance Targets
| Operation | Target | Description |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| Create | < 1ms | Single issue creation |
| List (1k) | < 10ms | List 1000 issues |
| List (10k) | < 100ms | List 10000 issues |
| Ready (1k/2k) | < 5ms | Ready query with 1k issues, 2k deps |
| Ready (10k/20k) | < 50ms | Ready query with 10k issues, 20k deps |
| Export (10k) | < 500ms | Export 10k issues to JSONL |
| Import (10k) | < 1s | Import 10k issues from JSONL |
| Search | < 100ms | FTS search on 10k issues |

### Benchmark CI Integration
```yaml
# .github/workflows/bench.yml
- name: Run benchmarks
  run: cargo bench --bench storage_perf -- --noplot

- name: Compare with baseline
  run: |
    cargo bench --bench storage_perf -- --save-baseline new
    critcmp baseline new
```

### Memory Profiling
```rust
#[cfg(feature = "profile")]
fn profile_memory() {
    use jemalloc_ctl::{stats, epoch};

    epoch::advance().unwrap();
    let allocated = stats::allocated::read().unwrap();
    let resident = stats::resident::read().unwrap();

    println!("Memory: allocated={}, resident={}", allocated, resident);
}
```

## Benchmark Categories

1. **Storage Operations**
   - Create issue
   - Update issue
   - Delete issue
   - Batch operations

2. **Query Operations**
   - List all
   - List with filters
   - Ready query (blocked_issues cache)
   - Search (FTS)

3. **Sync Operations**
   - JSONL export
   - JSONL import
   - Full sync

4. **Dependency Operations**
   - Add dependency
   - Cycle detection
   - Critical path calculation

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Benchmark framework with criterion
- [ ] Storage operation benchmarks
- [ ] Query operation benchmarks
- [ ] Sync operation benchmarks
- [ ] Performance targets documented
- [ ] CI integration with baseline comparison
- [ ] Memory usage benchmarks
- [ ] Benchmark results in README

## Dependencies
- Requires `criterion` crate (already in Cargo.toml)
- Requires core storage operations implemented
- Requires JSONL sync implemented

## Rationale
Performance benchmarks ensure br is fast enough for large projects and doesn't regress over time. The blocked_issues cache optimization must be verified with realistic dependency graphs. CI integration catches performance regressions before release.
